{{#content "body"}}
<div class="container">

<!-- Really didnt know how to inegrate this, so this works on its own -->


<!-- Example calendat embeding -->
<div class="row justify-content-center">
<h1> Google Calendar Embedding, Free, fast, easy, but looks kinda eeh </h1>
<iframe src="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/b/1/embed?height=600&amp;wkst=1&amp;bgcolor=%234285F4&amp;ctz=America%2FNew_York&amp;src=b3JjdXMwNTBAZ21haWwuY29t&amp;color=%23039BE5&amp;showTitle=0&amp;showNav=1&amp;showDate=1&amp;showPrint=0&amp;showTabs=0&amp;showCalendars=0&amp;showTz=0" style="border-width:0" width="800" height="600" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>
</div>
<hr class="my-5" />
<h1> Bravenet, looks better, but not ment for this kind of embedding, so some of the options are out of place </h1>
<iframe src="http://pub2.bravenet.com/calendar/show.php?usernum=103858403"  style="border-width:0" width="1200" height="1000" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>
<!-- How to make an embedding -->
<hr class="my-5" />
<h1> Time.ly has a nicer view, aswell as multiple view options </h1>
<script src="https://calendar.time.ly/embed.js" data-src="https://calendar.time.ly/5h3innqu/month" data-max-height="0" id="timely_script" class="timely-script"></script>
<hr class="my-5" />
<h1> Time.ly scroll </h1>
<script src="https://calendar.time.ly/embed.js" data-src="https://calendar.time.ly/5h3innqu/slider" data-max-height="0" id="timely_script" class="timely-script"></script>
<hr class="my-5" />
<h1> Tockify has a lot of custom setting if you choose to do it that way (plus only dark theme option) </h1>
<div data-tockify-component="calendar" data-tockify-calendar="eric.robertson" style = 'width: 100%; height: 800px;'></div>
<script data-cfasync="false" data-tockify-script="embed" src="https://public.tockify.com/browser/embed.js"></script>

<script>
    setTimeout(() => {
        /* adjust some sizing to view better*/
        document.getElementsByTagName('iframe')[2].style.width = '800px';
        document.getElementsByTagName('iframe')[3].style.width = '800px';
        document.getElementsByTagName('iframe')[5].style.width = '800px';
        document.getElementsByTagName('iframe')[5].style.height = '800px';

    }, 1000);
</script>



